<item>
            <title>[SPR-1768] ScriptFactoryPostProcessor looks for beans in local BeanFactory not in ApplicationContext</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1768</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Trying to set a property to a script (groovy script), that is not instrumented via ScriptFactoryPostProcessor yields NoSuchBeanDefinitionException &amp;#8211; because ScriptFactoryPostProcessor uses local BeanFactory (DefaultListableBeanFactory) which is not in any hierarchy with other BeanFactories in the application context.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="13468">SPR-1768</key>
            <summary>ScriptFactoryPostProcessor looks for beans in local BeanFactory not in ApplicationContext</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
