                            <comment id="16699" author="zregvart" created="Tue, 7 Mar 2006 03:29:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16700" author="zregvart" created="Tue, 7 Mar 2006 03:33:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch creates DefaultListableBeanFactory from application context using GenericApplicationContext.getDefaultListableBeanFactory, for this the ScriptFactoryPostProcessor was made ApplicationContextAware, for the test to work you need the patched version of groovy (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GROOVY-1262&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GROOVY-1262&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16711" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 7 Mar 2006 10:48:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report! Fortunately, this has already been fixed in CVS HEAD, and will be released in 2.0 M3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
